s interested in applying for r credit must obtain prior approval from an instructor in depth original research is required to obtain this credit number of units 2 course number 461 recently taught by sergio stone george d wilson all international and comparative law courses chinese law and business comparative corporate capitalism comparative law contemporary issues in international law and diplomacy designing liberation technologies european union law foreign affairs and the constitution foreign and international legal research international conflict management and resolution international criminal law international deal making international human rights international human rights and conflict resolution clinic international intellectual property international law introduction to organizational behavior latin american law law and terrorism theoretical and comparative perspectives law economics and politics of international trade legal writing for american practice spils law and society seminar spils research methods workshop state building and the rule of law workshop trade and investment in china transitional justice related links axess coursework digital reserve sls registrar mostly cloudy 50 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
